<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="403" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,790,1283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,397,790,815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[337,392,790,815]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
Guilan (
<bibRefCitation author="Modarres" box="[498,741,790,815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Modarres Awal, M. (1997) Platypodidae, Scolytidae. In: Modarres Awal, M. (Ed.), List of agricultural pests and their natural enemies in Iran. Ferdowsi University Press, Mashhad, pp. 185, 192 - 194." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Modarres Awal 
<number box="[682,741,791,815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Borumand" box="[754,940,790,815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Borumand, H. (1998) Insects of Iran: the list of coleoptera in the insect collection of Plant Pests and Diseases Research Institute: Coleoptera (XXIV), Curculionoidea, Fam. 162, 166 - 171 (Anthribidae, Attelabidae, Brentidae, Apionidae, Curculionidae, Scolytidae, Platypodidae. Plants Pests and Diseases Research Institute, Tehran, 110 pp." type="book chapter" year="1998">
Borumand 
<number box="[881,940,791,815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), Mazandaran and other northern provinces (
<bibRefCitation author="Modarres" box="[158,399,826,851]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Modarres Awal, M. (1997) Platypodidae, Scolytidae. In: Modarres Awal, M. (Ed.), List of agricultural pests and their natural enemies in Iran. Ferdowsi University Press, Mashhad, pp. 185, 192 - 194." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Modarres Awal 
<number box="[340,399,827,851]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[419,464,827,850]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Iran</collectingCountry>
(no locality cited) (
<bibRefCitation author="Knizek" box="[684,834,826,851]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Knizek, M. (2011) Platypodinae and Scolytinae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 7. Curculionoidea I. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 201 - 251." type="book" year="2011">
Knížek 
<number box="[774,834,827,851]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,790,1283]" box="[199,1275,862,887]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,451,862,887]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">General distribution.</emphasis>
Central and South Europe, North Africa, extending East to the Caucasus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="403" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,790,1283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,898,923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Biology.</emphasis>
Like the majority of 
<taxonomicName box="[538,636,898,923]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[538,636,898,923]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Platypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, it is polyphagous. In 
<collectingCountry box="[980,1025,899,922]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Iran</collectingCountry>
the following host plants have been recorded: 
<taxonomicName box="[270,469,934,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betulus">
<emphasis box="[270,469,934,959]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Carpinus betulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[490,619,934,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[644,831,935,958]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sativa">
<emphasis box="[644,831,935,958]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Castanea sativa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[852,962,935,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[987,1178,934,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Fagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[987,1178,934,959]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Fagus orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1199,1309,935,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" genus="Fraxinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="excelsior">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Fraxinus excelsior</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[269,378,970,995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oleaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Oleaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[398,490,970,995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[398,490,970,995]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Populus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName box="[548,672,970,995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Salicaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[693,787,971,994]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[693,787,971,994]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName box="[844,954,971,995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[975,1048,970,995]" class="Insecta" family="Tingidae" genus="Ulmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[975,1048,970,995]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Ulmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[1058,1100,971,994]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Scolytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spp">spp</taxonomicName>
. (
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1236,970,995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ulmaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ulmaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Modarres" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Modarres Awal, M. (1997) Platypodidae, Scolytidae. In: Modarres Awal, M. (Ed.), List of agricultural pests and their natural enemies in Iran. Ferdowsi University Press, Mashhad, pp. 185, 192 - 194." type="book chapter" year="1997">
Modarres Awal 
<number box="[151,211,1007,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The biology of the species has been studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Baker" box="[784,936,1006,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Baker, J. M. (1963) Ambrosia beetles and their fungi, with particular reference to Platypus cylindrus Fab. Symposia of the Society for General Microbiology, 13, 232 - 265." type="journal article" year="1963">
<collectingCountry box="[784,851,1006,1031]" name="United States Pacific Island Wildlife Refuges" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Baker</collectingCountry>
(
<number box="[868,928,1006,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="1963.0">1963</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation box="[951,1244,1006,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Belhoucine, L., Bouhrauoua, R. T., Dahane, B. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2011 a) Apercu biologique du Platypus cylindrus (Fabricius, 1792) (Coleoptera, Curculionidae: Platypodinae) dans les galeries du bois de chene-liege (Quercus suber). Orsis, 25, 105 - 120." type="journal article">
Belhoucine 
<emphasis box="[1087,1139,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1163,1222,1007,1031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
, and others. The mycangia have been described by 
<bibRefCitation box="[578,834,1042,1067]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Cassier, P., Levieux, J., Morelet, M. &amp; Rougon, D. (1996) The mycangia of Platypus cylindrus Fab, and P. oxyurus Dufour (Coleoptera: Platypodidae). Structure and associated fungi. Journal of Insect Physiology, 42, 171 - 179. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / 0022 - 1910 (95) 00056 - 9" type="journal article">
Cassier 
<emphasis box="[676,734,1042,1067]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[765,826,1042,1067]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="1996.0">1996</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It usually attacks stressed or dead trees. In the Mediterranean region, the species is involved in “oak decline”, especially where 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1145,1079,1102]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1051,1145,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees are stressed (e.g. 
<collectingCountry box="[1403,1436,1079,1102]" name="South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">De</collectingCountry>
<bibRefCitation author="Sousa" box="[151,382,1114,1139]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="De Sousa, E. M. R. &amp; Inacio, M. L. (2005) New aspects of Platypus cylindrus Fab. (Coleoptera: Platypodidae) life history on cork oak stands in Portugal. In: Lieutier, F. &amp; Ghaioule, D. (Eds.), Entomological Research in Mediterranean Forest Ecosystems. INRA Editions, Paris, pp. 147 - 168." type="book chapter" year="2005">
Sousa &amp; Incio 
<number box="[323,382,1114,1139]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Sall 
<emphasis box="[439,490,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[506,567,1115,1139]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2014.0">2014</number>
). The associated ambrosia fungi belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Inacio et al. 2008" authorityName="Inacio et al." authorityYear="2008" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiostomataceae" genus="Raffaelea" kingdom="Fungi" order="Ophiostomatales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1174,1282,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Raffaelea</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Inacio" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Inacio, M. L., Henriques, J., Lima, A. &amp; Sousa, E. (2008) Fungi of Raffaelea genus (Ascomycota: Ophiostomatales) associated to Platypus cylindrus (Coleoptera: Platypodidae) in Portugal. Revista de Ciencias Agrarias, 31, 96 - 104." type="journal article" year="2008">
Inácio 
<emphasis box="[1378,1429,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[151,211,1151,1175]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but numerous other genera of fungi have been found associated with the adult beetles and their galleries (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Belhoucine" box="[209,483,1186,1211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Belhoucine, L., Bouhrauoua, R. T., Meijeer, M., Houbraken, J., Harrak, M. J., Samson, R. A., Equihua-Martinez, A. &amp; Pujade- Villar, J. (2011 b) Mycobiota associated with Platypus cylindrus (Coleoptera: Curculionidae, Platypodinae) in cork oak stands of North West Algeria, Africa. African Journal of Microbiology Research, 5, 4411 - 4423." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="b">
Belhoucine 
<emphasis box="[345,395,1186,1211]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[411,469,1186,1211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2011.0">2011</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Inacio" box="[496,713,1186,1211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Inacio, M. L., Henriques, J. &amp; Sousa, E. (2011 a) Contribution of symbiotic fungi to cork oak colonization by Platypus cylindrus (Coleoptera: Platypodidae). Silva Lusitana, 19 (n o especial), pp. 89 - 99." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="a">
Inácio 
<emphasis box="[574,625,1186,1211]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[640,699,1187,1211]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
). It carries the canker fungus causing cork oak (
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1427,1186,1211]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suber">
<emphasis box="[1262,1427,1186,1211]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Quercus suber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) charcoal canker (
<bibRefCitation author="Inacio" box="[350,577,1222,1247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Inacio, M. L., Henriques, J., Guerra-Guimaraes, L., Gil Azinheira, H., Lima, A. &amp; Sousa, E. (2011 b) Platypus cylindrus Fab. (Coleoptera: Platypodidae) transports Biscogniauxia mediterranea, agent of cork oak charcoal canker. Boletin de Sanidad Vegeta, Plagas, 37, 181 - 186." type="journal article" year="2011" yearSuffix="b">
Inácio 
<emphasis box="[433,485,1222,1247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[504,562,1222,1247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2011.0">2011</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
), and is also a likely vector of a fungus causing the death of plane trees (
<taxonomicName box="[160,375,1258,1283]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Platanaceae" genus="Platanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Proteales" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[160,375,1258,1283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Platanus orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in the Mediterranean area and 
<collectingCountry box="[732,777,1259,1282]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Soulioti" box="[791,1013,1258,1283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" refString="Soulioti, N., Tsopelas, P. &amp; Woodward, S. (2015) Platypus cylindrus, a vector of Ceratocystis platani in Platanus orientalis stands in Greece. Forest Pathology, 45, 367 - 372. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / efp. 12176" type="journal article" year="2015">
Soulioti 
<emphasis box="[889,938,1258,1283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[952,1013,1258,1283]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" value="2015.0">2015</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
